<title type="html"><![CDATA[I looking for contact info for Okkun Medaka - composer of...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7917&amp;p=80730#p80730"><![CDATA[
That'd be Miyoshi, since in these days publishers left copyrights in hands of artist (e.g. AI graphics (c) would go to AI graphic, music would go to Okkun Medaka, code to their codes, but game as a WHOLE PRODUCT is copyrighted by hudson soft).<br /><br />Today, of course that've changed, but in the days Adventure Islands 1-4 were published was as I said.<br /><br />Dunno what about Japan law on this matter, since I don't know JPN copyright laws.<br /><br />//edit: And even if I am wrong, Mr. Okuyama still may want to make some new tunes for me if he'll feel nostalgic enough <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />. So if anyone has any contact info on him or in case if he's deceased can confirm it, I'd be grateful.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4924">darkhog</a> — Tue Jun 28, 2011 4:05 pm</p><hr />
